   <back>
      <fn-group xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
         <title>[Footnotes]</title>
         <fn id="d29e211a1310">
            <label>1</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e218" publication-type="other">
The classic discussion of Ramsey pricing is relevant here, but in itself has nothing to do with the 'merit
goods' arguments advanced here. See Atkinson and Stiglitz (1980) for an exposition of Ramsey rules.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d29e228a1310">
            <label>2</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e235" publication-type="other">
See Sen (1982) for an exposition of the capabilities approach. An accessible survey is provided by
Dasgupta (1986).</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d29e245a1310">
            <label>3</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e252" publication-type="other">
Absolute and relative are employed here in a slightly different way from that traditionally used. See Sen
(1984).</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d29e262a1310">
            <label>4</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e269" publication-type="other">
See Hammond, Helm and Thompson (1985 and 1986) on gas and electricity respectively.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d29e277a1310">
            <label>5</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e284" publication-type="other">
It should be noted that even if the failure relates to lack of information, it does not follow that provision
of information is necessarily superior to provision of the good directly.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d29e294a1310">
            <label>6</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e301" publication-type="other">
ee Kemsley, Redpath and Holmes (1980).</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d29e308a1310">
            <label>7</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e315" publication-type="other">
See Child Poverty Action Group (1986) for a more detailed description of the treatment of energy costs
in the supplementary benefit system.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d29e325a1310">
            <label>7</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d29e332" publication-type="other">
ee National Gas Consumers Council (1985) and Electricity Consumers Council (1985).</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
